"Penelope: Hey Evan, how are things going? It feels like ages since we last talked.\nEvan: Hi Penelope, I'm doing well, thanks! Things have been pretty hectic lately, but in a good way. Lots of gigs, and I just got back from a really interesting place.\nEvan: Actually, I wanted to tell you \u2013 I was at Christian Reformed Church Jalingo fulfilling a lifelong travel goal. It was\u2026 quite an experience.\nPenelope: Oh, that sounds like you\u2019ve been occupied! Anything exciting happen with your music lately? Are you working on any new pieces?\nEvan: I am, actually. I\u2019m trying to incorporate some of the textures and rhythms I encountered during that visit into a new composition. It\u2019s still very early stages, but I think it has potential. It really got me thinking about different ways to approach harmony.\nPenelope: That sounds fascinating. You always manage to find inspiration in the most unexpected places. I'm currently leading a workshop for parents on managing screen time, which is proving to be quite a challenge!\nEvan: That sounds\u2026intense! Kids and technology are a whole world I don\u2019t really understand. It\u2019s good you're doing that work, though. It's so important.\nPenelope: It is rewarding, though often exhausting! I've been trying to practice mindfulness as a way to cope. Have you found any good ways to unwind when you're not at the piano?\nEvan: I've taken up birdwatching, surprisingly enough. It's really peaceful and forces me to slow down. Something about focusing on noticing small details is a good counterbalance to improvising.\nPenelope: Birdwatching! That's lovely. It's wonderful to find a hobby that brings you that kind of calm. I might have to give that a try sometime.\n\n\n\n"
